cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.LG, cs.ST. 

The paper deals with kernel density estimates, which are commonly used in computational geometry (cs.CG) and statistics (cs.ST). The concept of subset approximation is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), while the study of discrepancy falls under information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the use of smoother range spaces and the analysis of their size and discrepancy is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG).
